<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 2:51PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central Iron
County through 330 PM MDT...
At 250 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles southeast of Ursine, moving south at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Modena and Hamlin Valley.
This includes the following highways...
Utah Route 18 near mile marker 47.
Utah Route 56 between mile markers 1 and 24.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
